    "title": "Immediate Requirement Software Engineer at Schneider Electric India",
    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Schneider Electric India. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Software Engineer to strengthen our Tiruchirappalli-based team.\n\nAbout Schneider Electric India:\nSchneider Electric India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Write and execute unit tests and integration tests\n• Deploy and manage applications on cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP\n• Participate in on-call rotation for production support\n• Participate in code reviews and contribute to technical discussions\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n• Implement new features based on product requirements\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product, design, and QA\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in CI/CD\n• Proficiency in Git\n• Proficiency in TensorFlow\n• Proficiency in Kubernetes\n• Proficiency in Agile/Scrum\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Python\n• Proficiency in MongoDB\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Schneider Electric India!",
